Kagwe said healthcare workers will be the first to receive the doses. 

Kenya has recorded 106,470 coronavirus cases since March 2020, with 1,863 deaths. Strict precautions will be taken in the management of waste related to vaccination. 1.02 million AstraZeneca vaccine doses arrive in the country early tomorrow. Cabinet Secretaries, Principal Secretaries and politicians are top on the priority list for the vaccine against the deadly virus alongside health workers. The planning and coordination of the vaccine rollout will take up Sh53.4 million. WHO says the potential benefits of AZD1222 outweigh the known and potential risks.